""" Gives you water budget time series components from a MODFLOW -2005 simulation.
When both storage in and storage out are represented in +ve absolute values, then if storage in -storage out if negative means
aquifer is gaining water and water levels are rising.
absolute storage_in represents water levels falling and aquifer losing water
absolute storage out means water levels rising and aquifer gaining water.
from the flow system water is moving out to the storage
"""


"""" This code will work well only for full budget of model domain, when all cells are used
It is not a zone budget code"""


